Ok, ok, so perhaps they're not the MOST unconnected, but they certainly don't seem to have figured out how to get people as much free internet or even cheap internet as in the U.S.&nbsp; Can anyone explain this to me?&nbsp; Also, I am now willing to help financially encourage any tour team with even a hope of defeating Deutsche Telecom.&nbsp; That's right, I am after this company.&nbsp; I want to see the damn pink jerseys lose terribly!&nbsp; 

Beer is good =D&nbsp;

Film Festival: 
Very good!&nbsp; Much much better than I thought it would be.&nbsp; Friday night Nicholas and Harry went to see Whole Hog and Hot Chickan.&nbsp; Both of those sounded like good documentaries.&nbsp; Then I joined them for the short movie block featuring "Me Room Matey" and "Chalk" with others in between.&nbsp; Some friends of ours went to a gay fraternity slasher film that was filmed on Mud Island; just think about it!&nbsp; Then we went to Long Shot to listen to the blues man from St. Louis play.&nbsp; He was in a documetary that showed Friday, but the director did a shity job from what I've heard.&nbsp; Anyway, the blues guy performed well and had awesome pimp outfits.&nbsp; Long Shot was not nearly as crowded as normal.&nbsp; Dr. Wrobel totally cock blocked Dr. Lobur over Nicholas' professor Bowman.&nbsp; Maggie explained that she hated most white people who listened to blues b/c they often said thing like, "Oh, he's speaking about my life!" while wearing L.L. Bean or Prada.&nbsp; C'mon!&nbsp; Maggie is from Clarksdale (and white).&nbsp; We both agreed to never be those people and just enjoy the genre without trying to relate.&nbsp; We left and went to Jubilee and saw Marty, Glenn and Kelsey.&nbsp; It was very, very nice to talk with Glenn and Kelsey.&nbsp; I ended up hanging out with them during the film festival.&nbsp; We have a bond over not being in Wrobel's entourage.&nbsp; Kelsey's cool. Ok, end Kelsey love fest.&nbsp; 

Saturday we went to Animation Show and it was wonderfully funny except this one french film.&nbsp; Then we went to a documentary set that had a documentary about a health clinic in Jonestown, MS, one about a wildlife photographer in MS, and one about a NOLA resturant owned by a 92 year old grandma.&nbsp; The Jonestown health clinic was my fave.&nbsp; Then we watched Wristcutters.&nbsp; It was quite nice.&nbsp; 

K, I guess that's QUITE long enough.&nbsp;

- Beginner kickboxing is good.&nbsp; 
- Rainy days suck.
- I will present a paper on Celtic Feasting in Feb.
- I am ready for school to start back or me to become a housewife.&nbsp;

Christmas and New Years went well.&nbsp; We stayed in Oxford and most relatives came here.&nbsp; Nicholas' family went to Disney the week before Christmas and stopped in Oxford two days before Christmas on they're way home.&nbsp; That was nice.&nbsp; We at lunch and they came back to our apt for coffee and blueberry coffee cake.&nbsp; Chorni behaved nicely (mostly b/c we did what Ceasar said...).&nbsp; However, he did eat the rest of Natalie's cake.&nbsp; He looked at it and he looked at us with that "I know I'm not supposed to, but..." look.&nbsp; He then barely licked it and Natalie pointed out to us that he was about to eat it.&nbsp; We asked if she was going to finish it and since she wasn't we let chorni have it.&nbsp; I just love that he seemed to be sneaking and asking permission at the same time.&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; My grandmother's car wouldn't start Christmas Eve day so the day after Christmas, Nicholas and I took her back to Memphis.&nbsp; She took us to lunch at this great pizza place called Memphis Cafe Pizza.&nbsp; It was very good.&nbsp; We then bid her farewell (her car did start again that day, before we left) and went to run some errands.&nbsp; We ended up at this music store that had some used albums and bought quite a few good ones.&nbsp; They range from Tchaikovsky to Kansas.&nbsp; Yes, Kansas (Nick's pick, not mine).&nbsp; Btw, we did get a turntable for Christmas and it totally rocks.&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New Years was nice.&nbsp; We sat around reading and watching tv and went to Peter's for a bit.&nbsp; It wasn't our crowd so we left shortly after arriving.&nbsp; At home we broke out the first champagne bottle and watched the New York feed and Scrubs.&nbsp; After midnight we were off to watch The Office...British version bloaks.&nbsp;&nbsp; After that....well, I'm not allowed to post ;)&nbsp; 

I turned in my vague abstract last night.&nbsp; We'll see if the deadline was actually pushed back and if I'll be scrambling to actually put together a presentation.&nbsp; I still haven't quite found an angle to claim on Celtic feasts.&nbsp; 

Hope everyone is doing well!&nbsp; Happy New Year!&nbsp;

