I hope everyone has happy holidays and that no one is driven too crazy by relatives.&nbsp; David, Holla!

The GIS lab has been my home for the last couple of days.&nbsp; Especially today.&nbsp; In fact, I'm here now and won't leave until 5pm.&nbsp; I guess that's kinda bad...sitting around for so long.&nbsp; But, I'm going home and cleaning later.&nbsp; 

Fun with Critters:
&nbsp; Saturday night we came home from a halloween party and there was a 6 point buck just walking around in front of the apartments.&nbsp; He really didn't seem to care that we had interrupted his stroll until we got closer.&nbsp; 

&nbsp; Sunday afternoon we went to the grove to read and took the dog with us.&nbsp; We tied him up to the picnic table with the 20ft leash.&nbsp; Two squirrels played in the tree, chasing one another.&nbsp; However, upon their boisterous return from another tree, one squirrel didn't grasp the end of the branch well enough and fell about 30ft.&nbsp; Chorni took off after it.&nbsp; His leash ran out and he was snapped backwards in an amazing up and over&nbsp; back flip.&nbsp; Poor thing.&nbsp; It only added injury to insult of&nbsp; no squirrel.&nbsp; 

